Champion of Brell <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukallikamerov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalli Kamerov</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 418<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/14/01 2:52:17 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/895/90/28959015.jpg width = 135 height = 184></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ENC Epic....</span><hr size=1> I'm not really pushing for my epic, but it seems that the essence from hate drops an average of once per hate raid, but usually in bunches, ie, 2 one night, 0 the next.<br>
<br>
*shrug* in the 10 raids or so since it started dropping I probably could have 15 of the things by now considering all of the ones that rotted.<br>
<br>
As for the shissar head, that seems to be a luck of the draw, I go to fear fairly often to help friends / guildies get armor, I feel that sooner or later I'll get the head and then start my epic, but I'm not going to whore myself out begging to get on raids with cazic up like certain enchanters have been doing.<br>
<br>
Then again, considering they're almost certaintly patching the planes tomorrow, I'm just going to wait and see what the change is, since I doubt if they make cazic as tough as expected that the shissar will spawn after some other mob's death. (my guess would be draco or the new and improved fright / dread / terror).<br>
<br>
The rest of the enchanter epic seems pretty easy, just a bunch of short quests or things to do while on raids, and of course going into a few different cities to kill some npcs.<br>
<br>
<br>
Kalli Kamerov<br>
54th Enchantress<br>
Poison Arrow<br>
